Yambol is in southeast Bulgaria.  See <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yambol" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yambol</a>

Lozengrad is the Bulgarian name for the Turkish town Kırklareli, formerly known as Kirk Kilisse.   See <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K%c4%b1rklareli" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K%c4%b1rklareli</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Kirk_Kilisse" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Kirk_Kilisse</a>
To quote: &quot;The Battle of Lozengrad was part of the First Balkan War between the armies of Bulgaria and the Ottoman Empire. It took place on 24 October 1912, when the Bulgarian army defeated an Ottoman army in Eastern Thrace.&quot;
